cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with 3D point cloud segmentation using a neural network that learns both 2D textural appearance and 3D structural features. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also explores synthesizing camera poses in 3D reconstructed scenes, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper deals with global context priors, which involves graphics (cs.GR) techniques.
